
// This Hyperlambda snippet replaces occurrences of a specific string in a node's value. It uses [set-value] to change the value of [.result] by invoking [strings.replace] on the same node. The [strings.replace] slot searches for the string specified in [.rtl] and replaces it with "true". The process involves evaluating the current value of [.result], performing the replacement, and then updating [.result] with the new string.
set-value:x:@.result
   strings.replace:x:@.result
      .:[[rtl]]
      .:true
